# ── Rust build artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────────
/target/
**/target/
**/*.rs.bk
# (Cargo.lock is intentionally NOT ignored — we ship apps, want reproducible builds)

# ── External tool checkouts (multi-GB clones, each with its own .git) ──
/splat-tools/

# ── Pipeline run outputs ──────────────────────────────────────────────
/splat_run/
**/exports/
**/undistorted/
**/sparse/
*.db

# ── Gaussian-splat / 3D data (large binaries — keep them out of git) ──
*.ply
*.splat
*.ksplat
*.spz
*.sog
*.ssproj
*.gcloud

# ── Capture dumps ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.mp4
*.mov
*.mkv
**/images/
**/frames/

# ── Bevy / wgpu app assets that are large binaries ────────────────────
**/assets/**/*.ply
**/assets/**/*.gcloud

# ── Branded mesh assets (deFEEST / Bornhack Ægg / hardware / bitterbal) now live
#    in-repo with provenance — see USAGE.md. bawl-e.dae (bawlsec.com, a friend of
#    deFEEST) is a pending keeper, not published yet. ──
assets/bawl-e.dae
# Third-party party logos kept LOCAL (placeholders / greetings) — not ours to publish.
assets/evoke-23.*
greetings-logos/

# ── Camera-path scratch (default MARTIN_WAYPOINTS target; name a keeper differently) ──
/waypoints.json

# ── Local agent / editor / OS state ───────────────────────────────────
.claude/
.DS_Store
*~
*.swp
.idea/
.vscode/

# ── Mesh→splat bake outputs (Blender renders + Brush .ply) ──
/mesh_splat_run/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
assets/hd-test.png

# full-length reel render scratch
/_render/
/*.mp4
*.wav
assets/badge-front.png
assets/badge-back.png
assets/greetings-logos

# Local preview renders (not committed) — keep them out of the repo root, in /renders/
/renders/
*.mp3
/intro-preview.show

# MIDIs are generated, not shipped: score exports (pipeline/score_to_midi.py, e.g. op-de-camping.mid
# in the root) + copyright transcription refs under assets/. Regenerate on demand.
/*.mid
/assets/*.mid

# local mesh->splat A/B render artifacts (not assets)
mesh-ab/

# scratch greetings crawl — not used in current demos, intentionally untracked
greetings.seq

# Large external splat demo assets (Mosure's go-board + trellis). They exceed GitHub's 100 MB file
# limit, so they live in assets/ locally but are NOT committed — fetch them with
# `pipeline/fetch-demo-assets.sh`. /scratch/ is a throwaway dir for experiment artifacts.
/assets/go_trimmed.ply
/assets/trellis.glb
/scratch/

# Production captures: real splats are large + personal — track the manifest, not the data
productions/*/captures/*.ply
productions/*/captures/*.glb
